Azure resources are individual components such as virtual machines, storage accounts, databases, and networks that are used to build cloud solutions. Resource Groups are logical containers that hold related resources.

For example, a web application may include:

* A virtual machine
* A database
* A storage account

All these resources can be grouped under a single resource group.

A real-life use case is project-based organization. A company can create separate resource groups for different projects, making management and billing easier.

Another example is lifecycle management. Deleting a resource group automatically deletes all resources within it, which is useful when cleaning up test environments.

Resource groups simplify resource management, access control, and cost tracking.
